process (Proc ∈ 1.. N)
This statement begins a collection named Proc of N processes, each process
identiﬁed by a number in 1.. N. The statement
variable j ;
declares j to be a local variable of these processes, meaning that each of the
N processes has its own separate variable j. A local or global variable z can
be initialized by a declaration of the form
variable z = exp ; or variable z ∈ exp ;
The matching “ {” and “ }” enclose the code for each process in the
collection Proc, where self is the identiﬁer of that process (in this example,
a number in 1..N).

